radiographic_examinations.findings: Lung bases are clear without pleural or pericardial effusion. The liver, spleen, gallbladder, pancreas, and adrenals appear normal. The kidneys demonstrate symmetric contrast enhancement and brisk excretion with incidental note made of extrarenal pelvises bilaterally. A fat-containing lesion within the right upper pole likely represents an angiomyolipoma. A lap band is positioned in standard configuration around the distal esophagus. The stomach is decompressed. A lap band injection port is normal in appearance. A connective tubing appears intact. The visualized loops of small bowel are normal in caliber and enhancement. The small bowel mesentery is normal. The pelvic organs are normal in appearance. The bladder is unremarkable. There is a 2.0-cm left adnexal cyst. The colon appears normal. The appendix is unremarkable. There are no concerning lytic or blastic osseous lesions.
